{"questionId":"e5d516e8-dc0a-449f-9696-276e786df83f_5","correctAnswer":"C","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up","content":"Evaluate $g(18)$ using the given function $g(x) = \frac{8}{9}x - \frac{4}{9}$."},{"title":"Solve","content":"$$g(18) = \frac{8}{9}(18) - \frac{4}{9} = \frac{144}{9} - \frac{4}{9} = \frac{140}{9}$$"},{"title":"Answer","content":"<strong>C</strong> is correct."}]}